1. Download sifive sdk
    git clone --recursive https://github.com/sifive/freedom-e-sdk.git

2. Download sifive toolchain
    https://www.sifive.com/software, Down load Prebuilt RISCâ€‘V GCC Toolchain and Emulator

3. cd freedom-e-sdk-xxxxx/bsp, add cva6 bsp
    you can copy sifive's bsp, then modify .dts .h according to cva6
    attention: 1)modify clint address and plic address;
               2)plic interrupt max priority is 7;
               3)modify clock to 25MHz;
               4)modify plic registers' address used for debug;
               5)must modify metal.default.lds; 
               6)must add your include dir to Makefile;
               7)must generate .bin file;
               8)use download_firmware.py to download firmware to memory;
4. Create your own project use the forllow command:
    make PROGRAM=hello TARGET=cva6 INCLUDE_METAL_SOURCES=1 STANDALONE_DEST=/path/to/desired/location standalone

5. Set riscv toolchain dir: 
    export RISCV_PATH=/path/to/toolchain/you/download

6. chmod -R 777 xxx/  if you get permission denied error
